Project 2: Supervised Learning - Classification¶

Data Description:¶

The file Bank.xls contains data on 5000 customers. The data include customer demographic information (age, income, etc.), the customer's relationship with the bank (mortgage, securities account, etc.), and the customer response to the last personal loan campaign (Personal Loan). Among these 5000 customers, only 480 (= 9.6%) accepted the personal loan that was offered to them in the earlier campaign.

Domain: Banking¶

Context:¶

This case is about a bank (Thera Bank) whose management wants to explore ways of converting its liability customers to personal loan customers (while retaining them as depositors). A campaign that the bank ran last year for liability customers showed a healthy conversion rate of over 9% success. This has encouraged the retail marketing department to devise campaigns with better target marketing to increase the success ratio with minimal budget.

# Fit the model on train
lr_model = LogisticRegression(solver="liblinear")
lr_model.fit(x_train, y_train)
#predict on test
y_predict = lr_model.predict(x_test)


coef_df = pd.DataFrame(lr_model.coef_)
coef_df['intercept'] = lr_model.intercept_
print(coef_df)
model_score = lr_model.score(x_test, y_test)
print("Train Accuracy with Logistic Regression = ",lr_model.score(x_train, y_train) )

Task7: Give your reasoning on which is the best model in this case and why it performs better? (5 marks)¶

  1. All three models performs with the similar accuracy results around 90 %.
  2. But from the train and train accuracy observations KNN shows it is overfitted on the data and shows 100 % train accuracy and 89% of test accuracy.
  3. Logistic regression shows train accuracy of 91% and test accuracy of 90%.Naive Bayes also shows 88.91 % train accuracy and 89.6% test accuracy.
  4. Also precision and recall of Logistic regression and Naive Bayes model is good compared to KNN model.
  5. So, from all above observations Logistic regression and Naive Bayes fits well on the given dataset.
  6. The dataset is small and independent variables are not co-linear so Logistic regression and Naive Bayes performs well.KNN assumes outliers should be treated prior to training which is not done here.
